betterquesting:10.desc:8:
These items will get you going straight away, but perhaps challenge yourself not to accept them and craft manually? 

Warning, this will require a lot of iron mined underground.

Most technology has to be researched before you can craft or use it. This is achieved by crafting science packs, the more advaced the technology, the more advanced and the greater number of science packs that are required.

The science pack is then converted to research points in an Laboratory which can be spent unlocking new technology.

This is a key aspect of this pack, and will require a lot of resource management.

Use your newly crafted Basic Assembler to start crafting Red Science Packs.

Green science packs provide access to the next tier of technology providing technology such as electronics and automation.


§bTip: Focus on automating Basic Circuits and locating redstone

The Penultimate Science pack to unlock even more advance technolgies.


§bTip: This research requires a lot of circuits. Add more automation for circuit building so that they do not become a bottleneck.

§b§eTip: This research also requires plastic, which is made from oil.

These Ultimate Science packs will unlock nanotechnogly, allowing for a mass amount of even more advanced and more importantly, smaller machines.

§bTip: This research requires heavy usage of basic and advanced circuits. Keep an eye on your redstone and copper!

§eTip: Lots of crafting steps are required, automate each part seperately then combine

§aTip: Alternative recipe options might help, check all options before comitting yourself to a path.

Provides access to the Basic Assembler. This simple auto-crafting system will craft items made from 2 ingredients.

This is a 2x2x2 multiblock structure. The package can be shapeless crafted into a single use deployable capsule containing all the blocks.


Power: 210 RF/t
Pollution: 1.0 (Carbon)


Tip; Search JEI for the Basic Assembler Blueprint for a guide on how to build.

Tip: Use multiple Coal Generators or Bio Generators connected with LV connectors, relays and wires to power.

By combining the Inserter with circuits, we now have a way to sort items.

Provides the Item Router from Immersive Engineering and additional Logistical blocks from Logistical Automation.


Note: This block outputs to either an inventory or IE/LA belts.

To advance, Steel is needed for our industry. This is smelted in an Improved Blast Furnace. It can also smelt normal ores faster than the Stone Furnace.

Provides the Improved Blast Furnace from Immersive Engineering, which is made from Reinforced Blast Bricks (refer to the Engineer's Manual for details)


§bTip: Use mulitple blast furnaces to keep up with the Mining Drills and demands of your factory

§aTip: Use the first Steel to create the Steam Generator from Immersive Engineering (this is the Diesel Generator renamed)

Basic solar panel to generate power.


Generates from 25.6 RF/t with no pollution.

Burning coal is the only way to start generating power.

Only generates 60 rf/t and always burns coal, even if the generators small internal storage is full.

Useful to jump start the factory. Place next to the Power Input on the Metal Former to charge.

Provides additional Conveyor Belts.


Stage: L001

Provides a faster Conveyor Belt from Logistical Automation and the MagneticCraft Conveyor Belt (these allow backstuffing).


§bTip: Inserters can pick up from the LA Belt but may require a speed upgrade to do so!


§aNote: Items appear on both sides of the MagneticCraft Conveyor Belt, but Inserters will pull from both sides.

Provides the Advanced Circuit & Blue Science Pack, unlocking further research to many other technologies.


Stage: A012

The factory requires a lot of specific components, an Automated Workbench will craft these products automatically and in many cases more efficent on resource usage.

Provides the Automated Workbench structure.


Stage: A011

Provides the technology to transfer power at a faster rate.

Provides MV Wire, MV Connector & MV Relay.

LV wires have a max load of 4096 RF/t, connectors transfer 512 RF/t
MV wires have a max load of 16384 RF/t, connectors transfer 2048 RF/t

§a## UNLOCKS SPIDERS ##

§cWarning: If a wire exceeds it's max load, the wire will burn out. Too many connectors actively drawing their maximum will overload the wires.

By enhancing & fortifying a normal chest, you can now store a single type of item.

Provides the Single Spot Chest which stores 64 items, and the Advanced Bin which stores 2048 items.


Stage: L003

Provides the technology to transfer power at High Voltage and to transform that power to lower voltages.

Stage: R012

Provides the technology to store MV and lower power.


Stage: R022

Knowledge of Bio Fuels, a more eco-friendly oil source.

Provides the Squeezer, Fermenter and Refinery.


Stage: P023

A specialised machine to make ammo more efficiently.


Available as soon as Engines are researched.

Provides knowledge on how to make Plastic.

Plastic is made in the Chemical Plant Modular Machine structure, requiring Gasoline, Coal and 490 RF/t.

Stage: P024

Grants knowledge of Sulfur processing, providing access to further technologies.

Sulfur is crafted in the Chemical Plant Modular Machine by combining Gasoline and Water.

Stage: P025

Any good factory is going to need oil and the products you can refine from it.

Provides Dowsing Rod, Fluid Pump Component & MM Oil Refinery structures, allowing the production of Lubricant, Diesel & Gasoline.


Use the Dowsing Rod to locate oil in a chunk, place a 3x3 foundation of stone, then a 3x3x3 multiblock made from Fluid Pump Components.

§c§f
Stage: P013

Oil Refinery:
Power: 980 RF/t
Pollution: 1.0 (Carbon) 0.4 (Sulfur)

Fluid Pump:
Power: 210 RF/t
Pollution: 2.0 (Carbon) 0.2 (Sulfur)

§a## UNLOCKS WITCHES ##

Turning Ingots into Plates allows for a much more efficient use of resources when crafting advanced machines.

Provides the Metal Press structure.


Stage: P012

By slowly burning wood or coal, you can make charcoal or coal coke, plus also small amounts of creosote oil, but it's very polluting.

Provides the Coke Oven structure.


Pollution: 4.0 (Carbon) 0.4 (Sulfur)

Utilising more advanced technologies allows for more efficient solar panels.


Generates from 256 RF/t

Some of the machines require special alloys. A Kiln furnace will produce these.


Stage: P002

By combining powered heaters with the Blast Furnace, the smelting speed is increased.

Provides the Blast Furnace Preheater.


§a## UNLOCKS CREEPERS ##

The Arc Furnace is a powerful machine, using power instead of solid fuel to process ores and alloys.


Stage: P022

By crushing the ores before they are smelted you can double your ingots.

Provides the Crusher structure.


Stage: P021

This pack is themed on the Factorio style of progression, where technology is unlocked via research (this questbook). Many recipes for key components have also been adjusted to be similar to Factorio, with more streamlined resource requirements but also a higher resource requirement.

Providing resources, power and autocrafting are key to progress.

Unlike other questbook packs, don't work on one chapter at a time, explore each chapter to see what research is available next.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Making Light of a Dark situation
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Torches cannot be crafted in this pack. You need to research, build and power Lanterns to provide your light.

So you are not completely in the dark, here are some Lanterns that do not need power to get you started.

To progress through the military technology, a special science pack is required. With this you can unlock a large amount of armour and weapon options.

Tip: Look at all recipe options available for concrete
You are now ready to start building your factory. Have fun!

The chests and bins are a great way to store items, but their capacity is limited. A large silo will hold a 41472 of a single item.

A Shipping Container can also hold a lot of resources (165888 items) and be easier to integrate into automation, but it is more expensive.

Instead of having a lot of chests, a set of shelves that hold the chests can provide a nice central storage area.


Provides the Silo structure from IE, Shipping Container from MagneticCraft and Shelving Unit from MagneticCraft.

Stage: L013

Steam power is the key to generating a lot of power at the start.

To get started, build a boiler. This is a multiblock structure and can be of variable size.


Place first a layer of Firebox blocks including a Controller (GUI interface) and Hatch (to allow insertion of fuel).
On top of this, add Boiler blocks, include a Valve to pump in water, and a Vent on top to pump out steam.
(This will build a 3x3x5 Boiler)

The boiler has 3 fuel slots, once all 3 contain fuel the boiler will produce the most efficient amount of steam, likewise the bigger the boiler, the more efficient it is.

Place an Immersive Engineering Fluid Pump on top of the vent to extract steam. Unpowered it will slowly extract steam, but a powered pump will pull out steam faster.

Tip: IE Pump can be configured for input and output faces by hitting it with a hammer (Blue = Input / Orange = Output). The Pump also needs a Restone Signal to operate.

Note: IE Liquid Pipes don't always reconnect to the boiler on world load/chunk load. Recommend that the IE Pump connects to the boiler directly.


Pollution: 4.1 (Carbon)

Whats better than an axe for chopping down trees (or other limbs...), yes, a Chainsaw!

Stage: M901
If you need to get away from it all and do some manual mining, the Mining Drill is your new best friend.

Upgrading the Burner Drill to a Powered Drill removes the need for a Solid Fuel source, instead it will run off RF.

The Powered Drill is crafted from a Burner Drill (check JEI), and the 9 Drill Components are placed in a 3x3x1 layer to form the Drill.

Just like the Burner Drill, insert a Drill Head, and Shift Right Click a side to set the output.


Power: 210 RF/t
Pollution: 1.0 (Carbon) 0.1 (Sulfur)

Further advances in electronics.

Provides the Elite Control Circuit and the Fabricator, for crafting advanced energy based military technology.

Stage: A024
Allows the charging of RF storage items, such as batteries.

Provides the Advanced Assembler multiblock structure, this is an upgrade to the Standard Assembler, that operates faster.

Also provides the IE Assembler, the first available option for automatic 3x3 crafting recipes.


Advanced Assembler:
Power: 490 RF/t
Polllution: 0.00

Provides knowledge of Batteries.


Stage: R013
Provides access to advanced military items.

Titanium Ore needs to be refined in a Reaction Chamber. This is a 3x3x4 multiblock structure.

Place a 3x3 layer of Reaction Chamber Housing with a Reaction Chamber Controller replacing the middle block of the front of the machine. Next place 2 layers of Reaction Chamber Glass, then top the structure with a layer of Reaction Chamber Housing.

All processing in the Reaction Chamber requires a Reaction Chamber Heatray Focus. Some recipes are unstable and can consume the Focus. 

To refine Titanium, pump in Creeper Acid, set the fluid level to 30% and set the Focus level to 5.


Stage: P032
Environmently Friendly!

Redstone in wire form, for more flexible redstone signals.


§bTip; Use forge microblocks to seperate wire connections. Craft with a Saw and nearly any block.

The world can be a windy place, lets harness this energy.

Provides the Windmill.


Stage: R002

Flowing water can be harnessed for power with a Watermill.

Stage: R003

Provides access to the Cloche, an automated farm that grows a crop in its own environment. Just provide water and power.


Stage: A031

Additonal ways of handling fluids.

Provides the multiblock storage Tank (that can hold 512 buckets), a portable Tank (that can hold 8 buckets).

Also provides the Bottling Machine structure.


Stage: L002
Provides knowledge for Energy Based military technology.

Sometimes you just want to mine manually, there's something just so relaxing about digging. But it can be frustrating finding the right spot to mine.

A Seismic Vibrator will tell you what is in the overworld chunk by using a Seismic Reader you can anaylise a column of blocks within range of the Seismic Vibrator.

§bTip: The Seismic Reader requires power, build a Charging Station.

More ore and oil can be found deeper than the existing drills can reach. A Core Sample drill will tell you what can be found in the deepest depths.

Stage: P026

Finding a larger source of ores deep below bedrock is very useful, but a more advanced form of mining is required to access it.
Also provides access to Ores not found by the Drills, such as Titanium and Uranium.

Provides the Bucket Wheel Excavator from Immersive Engineering.


Stage: P031

Provides the Bolt Rifle for longer range firepower.


§a## UNLOCKS ZOMBIE VILLAGERS AND SKELETONS ##
Further improvements in armour allow the crafting of Combat Armour.
A suit of iron armour isn't going to offer the protection needed. Look at crafting a suit of Soldier's Armour.
Further improvements to the Combat armour to offer additional protection.
The ultimate armour, effectively a one man tank.

Research into the basic engine.

Unlocks the ATV vehicle.


§e§bTip: Place the crate, then right click with the Wrench from Crayfish to open. Requires fueling using the Crayfish Jerrycan.

§eTip: The Jerrycan can either be filled with Gasoline with an IE Bottling Machine, or coal can be used in a pinch.

Improvements on the basic Rails, and also provides the Cart Hopper, which quickly transfers items from/to the cart to another inventory.


Steel Rail - Suitable for long distances, carts will go faster on these, but don't use for turns!

Powered Steel Rail - Like the Powered Rail, boosts carts at insane speed.

Deceleration Rail - Slows carts slightly when given a redstone signal, useful if derailing is an issue.

An improvement over the combustion engine. Engines for a greener future!

Also provides the Advanced Motor, a slightly faster motor for Advanced Rocketry Machines providing a x1.5 speed boost.


§a## UNLOCKS HOSTILE DRONES ##

Provides access to Grenades, Combat Shotgun & Incinderary Ammo, and unlocks the Military Science Pack.


Stage: M011

Putting Oil to military use.

Note: The Fuel tanks are filled in a Bottling Machine with Gasoline, and not any of the recipes that show in the Chemical Lab.


Stage: M014

Provides access to the Rocket Launcher.


Stage: M013

Teaches the ability the manipulate and produce light.

Provides access to the Powered Lantern from Immersive Engineering.


Stage: C004

Provides Laser knowledge, making further technologies available.

Unlocks the Laser from Mekanism, a power intensive, but long range (and deadly) laser that can only be fired in one direction.

Advanced technology that compacts existing logistical tranport methods into pipe form.

Provides access to Item Ducts, Impulse Ducts, Fluid Ducts, Leadstone FluxDucts, Servos, Filters and an even faster conveyor belt from Logistical Automation.


§bTip: No more wires!

§cWarning: Don't have inserters trying to interact with ducts, causes game crash and save corruption.

Provides access to the Grenade Launcher

Stage:  M012


Tip:
This does not destroy blocks

Dark matter has many strange properties, once of those is breaking an item down to energy, and converting it into other items.


Unlocks the Condenser Mk1



Stage: S003

Knowledge of Explosives, when TNT just isn't good enough.

Required for Explosive Military technology, and also provides Obsidian TNT, Mining Charges and Advanced Mining Charges.


Stage: C003
Nuclear based military technology.

Provides knowledge of working with Flammable materials.

Allows research into Missile Launchers and Flame Throwers.

Provides acess to Carbon Fibres. They are crafted in a Chemical Labratory and mainly used for advanced military technology.


§a## UNLOCKS ENDERMEN ##

Specialised Science Packs that improve the production capacity & speed of your factory.

§bTip: This science utilises resources used throughout the factory. Plan carefully and don't starve areas of your existing factory of key resources.

Continual improvements to the circuits and provides the Precision Assembler. This research is also a requirement for Nanotechnology and Space Exploration.


The Precision Asssembler is a Mutliblock structure from Advanced Rocketry.


Stage: A033

By applying lubrication to specific machines, they can run faster.


Stage: L012
Provides blueprint for Electrodes.
Provides blueprint for Common Components.
Provides blueprint for Crafting Components.
Provides blueprint for Logistic components.

Automating growing and harvesting crops & trees might prove useful.

Provides the Farm structure and Thermonic Fabricator.


Stage: A021

The first ultimate challenge, for infinite power!!!!


Note: This is a repeatable quest.

The primary moon has Osmimum and Unusual Ore, both required for advanced technology.

There's only one thing for it, launching yourself into space on a rocket. What could go wrong?


Tip: Follow the quest line to assist in setting up a rocket

Tip: Most of the Ores are deep underground, and need heavy industrial mining to obtain.



Stage: S001
Nanotechology allows for single block machinery and advanced concepts such as teleportation and digitial storage.

Provides HV capacitors.


Stage: R031

Anomaly science packs are created by a refining process with Unusual Ore located on the moon.

This ore is not useful by itself, but with advanced research, can unlock the secrets of Dark Matter.

§bTip: While an intially simple looking recipe, don't be deceived!

§eTip: Best place to find Unusual Ore and Osmium is on the moon, but mining drills will not work up there. Perhaps there's a more industrial mining option available?

§aTip: Don't waste uranium!
Stage: M903

The Tesla Coil is an interesting experiment, being able to discharge shocks.


Stage: R032

Who'd have thought powerful currents running through metal wires would hurt?

Provides access to insulated cables.



Stage: R023

Basic deployable turrets that will attack any hostiles within a short radius.

Only low damage, but better than nothing.
Provides blueprint for Engineering Components.

Lightweight but strong alloy required for space exploration.


Stage: P041
Also known as "Osta Steel", a unique alloy of Osimum, Steel & Titanium Alumide, provides the foundations of Nanotechnology.

Advanced methods for machining metals into plates, rods and gears.

Provides access to the Advanced Rocketry Rolling Machine & Lathe.


Tip: The different tiers of Motors will speed up AR machines.

Provides access to the enhanced motor, allowing Advanced Rocketry machines to operate at twice the speed.


Stage: A041

Ultimate motor, allows Advanced Rocketry machinery to operate at 4 times normal speed.


Stage: A051

Concrete is resistant to digging mobs.

Provides the ability to craft the various different types of Concrete.


Stage: M992

Tip: All styles of Concrete (modded and vanilla are available via Chisel)

Provides access to the Nuclear Reactor and is a requirement for Nuclear military technology.

Stage: R033

The Crusher will crush items to their dust counterparts, among other functions.

Stage: Z002

Test your factory to the limit with challenges. These provide Creative items as rewards.

Sounds Tempting....

Raw Ore can be purified with Oxygen or Flint to create ore clumps, resulting in 3x ore processing from a single block of ore.


Provides access to the Mekanism Purification Chamber.


Stage: Z011

Advancing on the idea of the Purification Chamber, the Chemical Injection chamber uses more complex gases (or Salt) to produce 4x ore processing.


Stage: Z021

By liquifying ore, "washing" out the impurities and crystalising the resulting slurry, you can achieve 5x ore processing.

The ore crystals may also have other uses.


Provides the Chemical Dissolution Chamber, Chemical Washer and Chemical Crystaliser.


Stage: Z031

Growing and purifying crystals provides access to even more advanced technology.


Unlocks the Advanced Rocketry Crystalizer.


Stage: P042

Smelts Ores into Ingots.


Stage: Z003

The Enrichment Chamber provides ore doubling in a single block, among other functions.


Stage: Z001

Osmium Compressor fuses materials with Osmium, producing specialised Mekanism alloys.


Stage: Z004

The Combiner will convert raw dusts back to their original ores.

That's useful right?


Stage: Z005

Who'd have thought that burning and processing fossil fuels would cause pollution?

Sucking it out of the air and passing it through a filter sounds like it would work right?

Provides access to the Pollutant Pump, Pipes, Advanced Filter Frame, Standard Carbon Filter and Standard Sulfur Filter.

Both Standard Filters have 16 capacity, and can be cleaned and reused.

Requires 100 RF/t to operate.

Provides the IE Distillation Tower, a much more efficient way to Refine Oil.


Stage: P034


Power: 980 RF/t
Pollution: 0.1 (Carbon) 0.01 (Sulfur)

The Metalurgic Infuser will combine one material with another, creating alloys and other items.

It's main use would be in creating Basic Circuits.


Stage: Z006

Allows many Mekanism machines to be upgraded to Factories, able to process multiple items at once.


Stage: Z013


Tip: Right Click the machine with the upgrade.

Additional tier of upgrade, allowing for more item processing.


Stage: Z023

Maximised item production within Factories.


Stage: Z033

Ultimate logicistic system, provides basic ability to store items digitially in a computer system.


Unlocks many items from Applied Energistics 2 with storage only on 1k drives.


Stage: L032

Provides access to the Quantum Entangloporter from Mekanism, allows the teleportation of items, energy & liquids instantly across any distance or dimension.


Stage: Z041

Provides access to the AE2 autocrafting system.


Stage: L044

A configurable mining system that mines by teleporting blocks from the world.


Stage: Z052

Thousands of Ingots have not been harmed by teleportation, so it's time to take it to the next level and send living bodies, such as yourself.


Unlocks the RFTools Dialing Device, Matter Transmitter and Matter Receiver.


Stage: Z051

Provides access to Signalum Servos and Filters.


Stage: L022A

Provides access to the Elite Bin, allowing for 32k items to be stored in a single block.


Stage: L013B

The ultimate storage solution in a single block, stores 262k items.


Stage: L013C
Provides access to Dense and Smart Cables, Level Emitters, large Storage Drives and more!

Allows the inserter to transport up to a stack at a time.


Stage: L023

Intermediate research stage providing knowledge about flight.

A requirement for Drones and also provides access to the Sports Plane.


Stage: A036

Intermediate research stage providing knowledge about robotics.

Provides access the Hauler Drone, a basic robot that will pick up items within a radius of a chest.


Stage: A034


§bTip: They get confused by IE Conveyor Belts and can be very derpy.

Logistic Drones provide a more efficient alternative to conveyor belts.


§bTips:
§fPlace frames on an inventory block to allow a Logistics drone to interact with that inventory. The type of frame will control the type of interaction (read tooltips!)

Right clicking an Framed inventory with a Logistics Configurator will allow the setting of filters and number of items/blocks.

Since drones use pressure as power, use a Flux Compressor to generate pressure. Put a Security Upgrade in the Compressor to prevent over pressure.

Using Charging Stations with Dispenser Upgrade to allow drones to automatically recharge themselves.

Provides access to a personal combat drone that will attack any hostile mob attacking the player.

Stage: M016


Tip:
Warning, the Drone AI will attack the player if the player damages the drone.

Allows the Inserter to operate faster.


Stage: L014

Not quite flight, but allows for powered jumping, greater fall distance and reduced fall damage.

Stage: M904

Strapping some gasoline fueled rockets on your back sounds a great way to fly.


Stage: M905

Next up, infinite fluids!

This is also repeatable
Final tier, creative items!

An advanced form of Battery, storing a larger amount of power.


Stage: R034
A space suit will protect you in space, it can also have extra modules installed to provide additional functionality, the bare mininum being a pressurized tank to hold Oxygen.

Water can be split into Hydrogen and Oxygen with an Electrolytic Separator. This may prove useful for later industrial use, but for breathable oxygen and hydrogen for Rocket Fuel it needs to be passed through a Modular Machinery Purifier.

The resultant oxygen can be piped into a Gas Exchanger, which when you stand on it with your spacesuit, any empty pressurized tanks will automatically fill with Oxygen.

By passing the collected energy through a relay, more collectors can be used.


Provides the Anti-Matter Relay Mk 1


Stage: S005

Rocket Fuel is refined in an Advanced Rocketry Chemical Reactor.

This requires 1000mb of Hydrogen, and 10 Solid Fuel and makes 1000mb of Rocket Fuel.


Note: The Chemical Reactor is a 2x2x3 multi-block structure, use the Holo-Projector to guide you in it's construction.

Improvements to the energy collector allow for faster collection of energy.


Stage: S014

Ultimate tier of the Energy collector


Stage: S024

Build a 3x3 flat area from the Launch Pad blocks, on one side, build up the structure tower blocks ensuring the bottom structure tower block is touching the launch pad.

Next assemble the rocket using the components indicated, the design of the rocket is flexible. Ensure it includes the Guidance Computer and a Seat.

Lastly place the Rocket Assembling Machine one block up from the Launch Pad blocks, and provide power.

In the GUI of the Rocket Assembling Machine, click Scan, and if the structure is valid, a frame will appear. It will proceed to scan the rocket, and inform you of any issues with the Rocket.

Then click Build to turn the blocks into an actual Rocket.

Shift-Right Click the rocket to bring up it's interface, it will show you the modules on the Rocket (Guidance Computer), and current fuel (empty). Place the Planet ID Chip in the Guidance Computer.

On the main rocket GUI, click the Choose Dest button, this will show the local planet and moons. Pick a moon as the destination.

Improvements to the relay allow for faster transmission of energy.


Stage: S015

Ultimate tier of the Relay.


Stage: S025

Improvement on the Condensor Mk1, allowing for items to be processed a stack at a time, plus a dedicated output area.


Stage: S013

Station Markers are used to automate item transportation by minecarts by providing nameable locations for carts to travel to.


§bTip: Research Rail Signals to unlock the full potential of Station Markers and Cart logistics.
§e
Tip: Right click a Cart with a Rail Configurator to program the destinations (Schedule) the cart must follow.

The strange crystals in this Unusual ore cannot be extracted by conventional crushing or smelting methods.

By combining Creeper Acid with Alien matter, the rock is dissolved away from the crystal and extracted from the solution by short range teleportation.

These crystals are of no use for industrial or military use, but can be useful to unlock one of the mystries of the universe.

Resonant Ender is made in an IE Mixer, and Unusual Crystals are used for Anomoly Research, which produces Dark Matter.

By collecting and focusing the energy from light you can create items from sunlight!

The collector can be placed next to the condensor and the energy will automatically pass into the condensor.


Stage: S004

To get started with logistics and automation, use Inserters, which will pull from one inventory, and place in another or onto Conveyor Belts, which can be used to move items over distances.

§bTip: The inserters have a GUI to allow whitelisting/blacklisting of items, and also two upgrade slots to improve speed and stack size.

§cWarning: Ensure items on the Conveyor Belts have a destination, otherwise items will spill into the world and cause lag.

Provides the ability to re-use Cyanite nuclear waste, and to enrich U-238 to make U-235.


Stage: R042

To extract that deep oil, a pumpjack is required.


Stage: P033

Enables Signals to organize multiple carts on a single Railway.

Provides access to the Block Signal and Chain Signal.



The Signal block must be placed to the right side of a rail track.

The Signal "keeps watch" over a strech of track (up to the next signal block). If the track has a cart on it already, the Signal will emit not emit a redstone signal and show a red light. Place 2 Powered Rails next to the signal, and any other carts will be stopped until the track is clear.

The signal will also handle track switching based on the desinations the cart is trying to reach, so it's always worth placing a Signal at each junction.

Holding anything Rail related will show colour coded lines on the rail track showing valid cart direction and the length of track being managed by a signal.

A lab converts the science packs into research points, to unlock new technologies.

The lab is a 3x3x3 multiblock structure. Search JEI for Laboratory Blueprint to see how it's built.


Exploring Boilers and Steam Generators on the Power Chapter would be a good next step, the Coal and Bio Generators will not be sufficient to grow your Factory.

§nKEY RESOURCES:

§§§n§n§r§o§l§7§o§lIRON§f - Key component for your factory, commonly refined into steel

§6§l§oCOPPER§f - Required for electronics, vital for advanced technology

§8§l§oHARDENED STONE §f- This special stone type is required for early tech. Normal stone just isn't good enough!

§c§o§lREDSTONE §e§f- This is Minecraft after all, redstone is still required.


§nOTHER RESOURCES:

§eGOLD, §fSILVER,§8 LEAD, §fALUMINIUM, TITANIUM, §2§aURANIUM, §bDIAMONDS, §2§a§2EMERALDS §fall appear as normal and will have specific uses. You'll need to ensure your automation lines don't mix these resources with your key resources, otherwise your factory will come to a halt.

0:10.description:8: Adds 640 Redstone to the chunk are standing in

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Manual mining will not provide the continous resources your factory needs. Instead construct Burner Drills.

The crafting of a Drill creates a single block "Package", shapeless craft this block to turn into the individual blocks to assemble the structure. This is done to aid later Autocrafting logistics.

The Burner Drill is a 2x2x2 structure (8 blocks as a cube).

Next Shift-Right Click to set where the Drill outputs then insert a Drill Head to start mining (Drill heads are crafted from either Iron, Steel, Diamonds, Titanium or Uranium).

To locate ores, right click in a chunk with your scanner. Multiple Drills can be placed within the same chunk.


With research you can build Electric Drills that cause less pollution.


Burner Drill:
Pollution: 4.4 (Carbon) 0.4 (Sulfur)

0:10.description:8: Adds 320 Iron Ore to the chunk you are standing in

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Provides access the Standard Assembler. This multiblock structure can craft recipes using up to 3 solid ingredients and 1 fluid ingredient, or it can be built with 4 solid ingredients.


Power: 350 RF/t
Pollution: 0.5 (Carbon)
Provides the blueprints to Science Packs

The Laser Drill is a mining device that can be placed on a space station to mine the planet below at the cost of an extreme amount of energy.

Co-ordinates can be speficied within the GUI and the planet will be physically mined.

The primary purpose of the railgun is to accelerate items to extremely high speed using a powerful magnet to essentially shoot items from one planet to its moon. 

The railgun is not powerful enough to transport item stacks between planets and its range is limited to bodies within the same system (including space stations). 

In order to allow cross dimensional item transfer, the railgun does act as a chunk loader and if the remote end gets unloaded somehow, the transfer will fail.

The railgun can be used to transfer items from one part of the planet to another part of the planet as well at a lower energy cost.

The space elevator is a multiblock machine that provides an endpoint with paired space elevators. Space Elevators can only transport players between bodies in the same system such as a planet and an orbiting station, two stations orbiting the same planet, or a planet and its moon. Space elevators cannot transport players between two seperate points on the same planet.

The gravity controller is a machine that can be used to manipulate gravity within a certain radius in exchange for energy. The gravity controller can also affect the direction of gravity. When activated it does have a warmup and cooldown time so effects are not immediate.

A more industrial version of the Biogenerator, produces 2000 RF/t from biomatter, and also produces waste materials such as Biogas and Fertilizer.


Tip: It will constantly consume fuel to produce power, even if power storage is full.

Tip: Use a Biogas Engine to burn the Biogas for extra power.

Your crafting at the start is limited to your personal crafting and a single Worktable and a 2x2 multiblock called the Metal Former.

The Metal Former is a very limited machine, able to turn iron into pipes, and copper into wires.

It is highly recommended you automate everything!


Note: You cannot craft vanilla Crafting Tables, but you can find Crafting Tables in villages and other structures, if you can find some way to bring them back to base.

Tip: Don't loose your Worktable, they need machinery to craft!

The Seismic Reader is an advanced scanner that will show you the precise locations of ores in a chunk via a small map. This saves you having to run around into every chunk and scan it manually.


To use, right click, allow it to scan the local area, then place the ore/item to scan for. Chunks containing this ore/item will highlight in a shade of white on the GUI map, the brighter the white, the greater the density. 

Use in conjunction with the Advanced Ore Scanner to quickly locate areas with the ores you require.

Tip: Always keep samples of ores stored safely.
